article.headline: Holman leads Shockers with 16
article.linkText: Wichita State shocks Austin Peay by 15
article.story: WICHITA, Kan. (AP) -- Fridge Holman scored 16 points and Jamar Howard had 15 as Wichita State beat Austin Peay 62-47 Saturday to snap the Governors' 14-game winning streak. Wichita State (18-8), which led 32-24 at halftime, led 48-41 with 7:48 left and then went on a 14-4 run. Howard scored seven in that rally, including a dunk that put Wichita State ahead 52-41, and then hit 5-of-6 free throws. Holman closed out that run with two more free throws. Austin Peay (17-8) was led by Adrian Henning with 18 points and six rebounds. Paul Miller finished with 12 points for Wichita State. The game was part of ESPN's "Bracket Buster," an event that highlights mid-major programs.
